119 in 2000.\n\n==Geography and climate==\nPort Heiden is located at {{coord|56|56|56|N|158|39|21|W|type:city}} (56.948949, -158.655745).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|51.4|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|50.7|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|0.7|sqmi|km2}} of it (1.28%) is water.\n\nPort Heiden has a [[subarctic climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''Dfc'').\n\n{{Weather box\n| collapsed =\n| location = Port Heiden, Alaska\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 57\n| Feb record high F = 55\n| Mar record high F = 54\n| Apr record high F = 62\n| May record high F = 75\n| Jun record high F = 81\n| Jul record high F = 87\n| Aug record high F = 82\n| Sep record high F = 73\n| Oct record high F = 64\n| Nov record high F = 55\n| Dec record high F = 59\n|year record high F = 87\n\n| Jan avg record high F =43.1\n| Feb avg record high F =43.2\n| Mar avg record high F =46.1\n| Apr avg record high F =49.7\n| May avg record high F =59.4\n| Jun avg record high F =65.1\n| Jul avg record high F =71.1\n| Aug avg record high F =72.1\n| Sep avg record high F =62.9\n| Oct avg record high F =55.2\n| Nov avg record high F =47.6\n| Dec avg record high F =43.4\n|year avg record high F =75.2\n\n| Jan high F = 28.5\n| Feb high F = 28.0\n| Mar high F = 32.5\n| Apr high F = 37.6\n| May high F = 46.5\n| Jun high F = 52.7\n| Jul high F = 57.3\n| Aug high F = 58.1\n| Sep high F = 53.6\n| Oct high F = 43.1\n| Nov high F = 36.2\n| Dec high F = 29.8\n|year high F = 42.0\n|Jan mean F = 22.5\n|Feb mean F = 21.9\n|Mar mean F = 26.3\n|Apr mean F = 31.9\n|May mean F = 40.6\n|Jun mean F = 46.9\n|Jul mean F = 51.9\n|Aug mean F = 52.9\n|Sep mean F = 48.1\n|Oct mean F = 37.6\n|Nov mean F = 30.7\n|Dec mean F = 24.2\n|year mean F = 36.3\n| Jan low F = 16.4\n| Feb low F = 15.8\n| Mar low F = 19.8\n| Apr low F = 26.0\n| May low F = 34.7\n| Jun low F = 41.1\n| Jul low F = 46.4\n| Aug low F = 47.7\n| Sep low F = 42.6\n| Oct low F = 32.1\n| Nov low F = 25.2\n| Dec low F = 18.5\n|year low F = 30.5\n\n| Jan avg record low F = \u22128.8\n| Feb avg record low F = \u22128.0\n| Mar avg record low F = \u22121.4\n| Apr avg record low F = 9.6\n| May avg record low F = 24.6\n| Jun avg record low F = 32.5\n| Jul avg record low F = 38.9\n| Aug avg record low F = 38.6\n| Sep avg record low F = 31.5\n| Oct avg record low F = 16.5\n| Nov avg record low F = 5.3\n| Dec avg record low F = -4.6\n|year avg record low F = \u221216.0\n\n| Jan record low F = \u221225\n| Feb record low F = \u221222\n| Mar record low F = \u221226\n| Apr record low F = \u22126\n| May record low F = 11\n| Jun record low F = 25\n| Jul record low F = 32\n| Aug record low F = 31\n| Sep record low F = 24\n| Oct record low F = \u22121\n| Nov record low F = \u22129\n| Dec record low F = \u221222\n|year record low F = \u221226\n|precipitation colour = green\n| Jan precipitation inch = 0.87\n| Feb precipitation inch = 0.50\n| Mar precipitation inch = 0.89\n| Apr precipitation inch = 0.74\n| May precipitation inch = 0.84\n| Jun precipitation inch = 1.10\n| Jul precipitation inch = 1.62\n| Aug precipitation inch = 1.97\n| Sep precipitation inch = 2.05\n| Oct precipitation inch = 2.22\n| Nov precipitation inch = 1.40\n| Dec precipitation inch = 1.03\n|year precipitation inch = 15.22\n\n|Jan snow inch = 11.3\n|Feb snow inch = 9.0\n|Mar snow inch = 6.9\n|Apr snow inch = 6.9\n|May snow inch = 1.8\n|Jun snow inch = 0.1\n|Jul snow inch = 0.0\n|Aug snow inch = 0.0\n|Sep snow inch = 0.0\n|Oct snow inch = 2.5\n|Nov snow inch = 5.8\n|Dec snow inch = 9.5\n|year snow inch = 53.8\n|source 1 = WRCC <ref name=\"climate\">[http://wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak7700 Port Heiden, Alaska - Period of Record : 9/1/1942 to 10/31/1988] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509021132/http://www.wrcc.dri.edu/cgi-bin/cliMAIN.pl?ak7700 |date=2017-05-09 }}. Retrieved November 10, 2019.</ref>\n|date=October 2019}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1880= 40\n|1890= 74\n|1920= 30\n|1930= 51\n|1960= 74\n|1970= 66\n|1980= 92\n|1990= 119\n|2000= 119\n|2010= 102\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=109\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\nPort Heiden first appeared on the 1880 U.S. Census as the unincorporated Aleut village of \"Mashikh.\"<ref>{{cite book|title=Geological Survey Professional Paper|url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_yCYlAQAAIAAJ|year=1949|publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office|pages=[https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_yCYlAQAAIAAJ/page/n62 49]\u2013}}</ref> Some maps erroneously placed it at the latter settlement of Port Moller instead of at Port Heiden. In 1890, it returned as \"Meshik.\" It next reported in 1920 as Port Heiden, and again in 1930. It did not appear again until 1960, but has appeared in every subsequent census. It formally incorporated in 1972.\n\nAs of the census<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 119 people, 41 households, and 23 families residing in the city. The population density was 2.3 people per square mile (0.9/km\u00b2). There were 56 housing units at an average density of 1.1 per square&nbsp;mile (0.4/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the city was 19.33% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 65.55% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], 2.52% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 12.61% from two or more races. 2.52% of the population were [[Race (United States Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Race (United States Census)|Latino]] of any race.\n\nThere were 41 households out of which 39.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 46.3% were married couples living together, 2.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 41.5% were non-families. 39.0% of all households were made up of individuals and 7.3% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.90 and the average family size was 3.79.\n\nIn the city, the age distribution of the population shows 39.5% under the age of 18, 5.0% from 18 to 24, 26.9% from 25 to 44, 22.7% from 45 to 64, and 5.9% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 33 years. For every 100 females, there were 105.2 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 125.0 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $31,875, and the median income for a family was $70,000. Males had a median income of $53,750 versus $21,667 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $20,532. There were no families and 5.6% of the population living below the [[poverty line]], including no under eighteens and 25.0% of those over 64.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Lake and Peninsula Borough, Alaska}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Alaska]]\n[[Category:Cities in Lake and Peninsula Borough, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Populated coastal places in Alaska]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|City in Alaska, United States}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Port Heiden, Alaska\n|settlement_type          = [[City (Alaska)|City]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    = <!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = NORTH SIDE AND WEST FRONT - St. Matrona Russian Orthodox Church, Po