to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|51.4|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|50.7|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|0.7|sqmi|km2}} of it (1.28%) is water.\n\nPort Heiden has a [[subarctic climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''Dfc'').\n\n{{Weather box\n| collapsed =\n| location = Port Heiden, Alaska\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 57\n| Feb record high F = 55\n| Mar record high F = 54\n| Apr record high F = 62\n| May record high F = 75\n| Jun record high F = 81\n| Jul record high F = 87\n| Aug record high F = 82\n| Sep record high F = 73\n| Oct record high F = 64\n| Nov record high F = 55\n| Dec record high F = 59\n|year record high F = 87\n\n| Jan avg record high F =43.1\n| Feb avg record high F =43.2\n| Mar avg record high F =46.1\n| Apr avg record high F =49.7\n| May avg record high F =59.4\n| Jun avg record high F =65.1\n| Jul avg record high F =71.1\n| Aug avg record high F =72.1\n| Sep avg record high F =62.9\n| Oct avg record high F =55.2\n| Nov avg record high F =47.6\n| Dec avg record high F =43.4\n|year avg record high F =75.2\n\n| Jan high F = 28.5\n| Feb high F = 28.0\n| Mar high F = 32.5\n| Apr high F = 37.6\n| May high F = 46.5\n| Jun high F = 52.7\n| Jul high F = 57.3\n| Aug high F = 58.1\n| Sep high F = 53.6\n| Oct high F = 43.1\n| Nov high F = 36.2\n| Dec high F = 29.8\n|year high F = 42.0\n|Jan mean F = 22.5\n|Feb mean F = 21.9\n|Mar mean F = 26.3\n|Apr mean F = 31.9\n|May mean F = 40.6\n|Jun mean F = 46.9\n|Jul mean F = 51.9\n|Aug mean F = 52.9\n|Sep mean F = 48.1\n|Oct mean F = 37.6\n|Nov mean F = 30.7\n|Dec mean F = 24.2\n|year mean F = 36.3\n| Jan low F = 16.4\n| Feb low F = 15.8\n| Mar low F = 19.8\n| Apr low F = 26.0\n| May low F = 34.7\n| Jun low F = 41.1\n| Jul low F = 46.4\n| Aug low F = 47.7\n| Sep low F = 42.6\n| Oct low F = 32.1\n| Nov low F = 25.2\n| Dec low F = 18.5\n|year low F = 30.5\n\n| Jan avg record low F = \u22128.8\n| Feb avg record low F = \u22128.